Read the implementation spec at `.hanness/pages/page_08_network_pvp.page` and implement everything described.

Prerequisites: page_01, page_02, and page_07 must be complete.

Steps:
1. Implement the full `server/index.js` as described (rooms Map, CREATE_ROOM, JOIN_ROOM, SET_READY, START_GAME, SEND_COMBINATION, DISPATCH_UNIT, SCOUT_START, KINGDOM_BUILD, disconnect handlers).
2. Create `client/src/network/SocketClient.js` wrapping socket.io-client.
3. Wire SocketClient into WaitingScene (ROOM_CREATED, ROOM_JOINED, READY_UPDATE, GAME_STARTING, COUNTDOWN, GAME_START events).
4. Wire SocketClient into GameScene (SYNC_STATUS → HUD.updateOpponent, SPAWN_UNIT → spawn enemy card, GAME_OVER → _onGameOver, SCOUT_REPORT → ScoutManager.onReport).
5. Wire kingdom build button click → socket.kingdomBuild(cards).
6. Wire PvP combine success → socket.sendCombination(cards).

After implementing, verify each acceptance criterion listed at the bottom of the spec.
